dct_title_s: Anglo-French advance between Lens and the Aisne
dct_alternative_sm: Supplement to the National Review, May, 1917
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by gradient tints, hachures, spot heights.
Legend includes "limit of Allies' advance to April 22nd."
Map shows railways, various roads, cities and villages, forests, various locations (such as forts, farms, hospitals, factories).
[Ancillary map]: Continuation south-eastward on same scale
